            <thetext>Steps to reproduce:

1) Load the Portal in Chrome (tested with 12 and 14)
2) Click and drag a portlet
3) Release the mouse button outside of the browser viewport
4) Move the cursor back inside the viewport. The portlet will still follow the cursor.
5) Click on on of the columns. The portlet will snap into place

So far, this is all known behavior. The problem/new behavior starts here:

6) Move the cursor around the columns. The portlet will jump between the various boxes even though no drag ghost is visible.</thetext>
